Nicki Breakdown: I broke down Nicki's verse and bars you may've missed while listening. I divided each line and bar description so that it will make it easier to find which line you want to know more about!   "I am the star in any room that stand in I am the stand out you just my stand-in" - The second "stand in" is referring to someone being a space filler for Nicki until she makes her return.   "These bitches copy my homework that's what they hand in" - This line could mean more than one thing. In school, if you didn't do your homework, you'd copy from another person's work and "hand in" your work to the teacher. Nicki is referring to her "sons" saying they are copying her every move and handing it in to their labels.   "That's why I'm private like the airports I land in" - This obviously explains her privacy and being a continuation of the previous line explaining why she is as private as she is.   "Life is a beach house don't let the sand in" - The reference to the beach house could be an analogy to life. Logically, you wouldn't want to get sand in your beach house because of the mess it tracks in. This could be applied to life as Nicki is describing her life and comparing that to the paradise of a beach house. The sand could be referencing not letting any "dryness" or "negativity" in her lavish life. "I ball in any arena go let the fans in" - This can describe Nicki's flexibility as an artist and as a human being in general. That public has to see how amazing she is.   "I should go cop a New Jersey that's word to Camden" - Camden is a city in New Jersey.   "These bitches time ticktocking better stick to dancing" - People dance on the hit social media app "TikTok" and she is using wordplay with the name to refer to time how much her "sons" don't have much time left.   "I D&G the wallet my money tall and brolic" - D&G is a brand and it's safe to assume Nicki has one or more D&G wallets. She uses the next word "money" to bounce off of D&G and goes on about her wealth.   "Big ass backyards just so Papa Bear could frolic" - Frolic means to play. She's letting us know that space won't be a problem for them!   "One Margherita pizza with parmesan and garlic" - This is just classic Nicki style to reference food in her raps. It's not a Nicki song unless she tells you what she orders.   "These bitches thirsty I could see why they alcoholics" -Â  This is a stand out line. Not only does it reference quenching a thirst, but there's a reason she said "alcohol" and not just water or anything else of that sort. This could mean that she peeps how people are setting themselves up by being "thirsty" and not receiving what they're reaching for.Â  Leaving them in a constant state of seeking approval and slight depression.   "Ain't gotta ever talk about when you are about it just bought a new car not to drive it but to walk around" - Nicki was talking Big Mac sh*t on this song and her ego, confidence, and presence was all there. Perfect for the early 2000s production they went for.   "Just call me Nicki cock the blicky the menage is silent" - Nicki as in herself â€¢ Blicky as in a gun â€¢ Menage as in threesome. It's a threesome between you, her, and the gun.   "Brand new vanilla Maserati I been HÃ¤agen-Dazs" -Â  HÃ¤agen-Dazs is an ice cream and she's describing the the color of her car. HÃ¤agen-Dazs was a word used to describe Denmark's fair treatment to Jews while WWll was happening. I don't know if it would be a reach to say that Nicki is also saying that she has been treating herself to good things. Double entendres. Her bars are crazy. "He call me solid even though I'm dripping water diet big booty sticking out my Daisy Dukes a' cause a riot" - Solid as in she's a real person. Dripping water diet as in she's everywhere. There's no doubt that Nicki's body has been a conversation that's thawed out as years go on. She knows she has people to fantasize about her which is what she explains.   "These bitches still my sons who could ever deny it" - This is true Nicki fashion. Anybody who knows Nicki knows that she has had plenty of "sons" in the game. Like she says, nobody can deny it.   "My packs hit different who could ever supply it" - Her "packs" as in her skill. Nobody can come close to what she has to bring to the game. No matter how many people come in, their "package" won't compare to hers.   "No one bitch could be my opp that shit offends" - It's no secret that acclaimed pushes have happened in this industry. No one's artist could compare to her, even though they may try to duplicate her.   "It's corporate giants and machines that went against me" - This adds on to her previous line only as in the business aspect of it and not anyone specifically. She's stating how much people with unknown names and faces in the industry tried to bring her down.   "I wash bitches man they couldn't even rinse me" - This line could mean that she cleans a person's career meaning it becomes non-existent. However the other "opponent" couldn't even turn on the faucet because that's how far behind they are compared to her.   "She say she hot I said well bitch come and convince me" - It's no question that Nicki is the queen. She's proven it time and time again and continues to do so. There's been plenty of rappers to flood on the scene and they say that their "hot" or the "hottest." She hasn't been convinced that, that's case and she wants to see them back that statement up.   'Ain't no C in green but I'm seeing green" - I think this is a slightly complex bar. She says "ain"t no c in green" listening to the lyrics I can assume that the "c" could stand for "Cash." She's seeing green as in she's seeing money.   "Even with them floor seats they couldn't see the team" - Floor seats are the very first row of seats that is located on the ground and not elevated like the rest of the seats are. "The team" being her, Wayne, and Drake. She's saying even with those seats you couldn't compete with them because they're too good.   "The K-I-N-G, THE GOAT, PLUS ME THE QUEEN" - Claiming their position in the rap game.   "I send shots send em' back or flea the scene" - This is another complex bar. She sends shot, meaning their coming from the gun. "Send em' back," meaning the other opponent stands their ground or punks out and fleas the scene. Kinda like she's testing them. Now calling back to shots and then she says "flea." She's coming back so hard that her "shots" will be painful as a "flea shot." Pen = unmatched   Nicki is an incredible artist and proves continuously whys she is who she is.

â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤â¤

Drake deserved the Billboard artist of the decade.  The man has more relevant hits than any other artist ever.  But Drake wouldn't have been as big without Nicki and Wayne.  Collaborative and competitive teammates are healthy.  So healthy, they are one the most successful ever.  But I say all that to say this:  Hearing Wayne on this track brought me back to mixtape Wayne.  When he took everyone else's singles and just recorded bars (sometimes no hooks).  Can we all take a moment to realize how seriously good his lyrics are: he said put you 6 ft deep, I'm being socially distant.

Drake started it off with a damn near quadruple entendre . " This not going to be the first time that I do numbers on two crutches".  4 meanings: 1.Drake's character on Degrassi was on crutches for while and him being shot boost the show ratings 2. Drake tore his ACL in 2009 on stage during that time he was the hottest name in music game selling crazy records from his "Best I Ever Had" single and So Far Gone mixtape that was repackaged as an Ep that sold over 700,000 going into 2010. 3. Recently he tore his meniscus which had him on crutches and was still the highest streamed artists of that year 4. Nicki Minaj and Lil Wayne are Drake's support (2  crutches) throughout his career and most of their songs together are multi-platinum as well as this song destine to be platinum or multi-platinum  Another double entendre from Drake's verse . " . "You niggas can't trouble me from the Double Tree" 2 meanings: 1.He's stunting on niggas saying you can't afford to be at places I stay, which is why you stay at the Double Tree hotel 2. In Toronto "tree" is also slang for number three, so he's  saying double 3 which equals 6 and 6 is the nickname for Toronto  This line is aimed at his haters from his city. He's telling them you niggas don't have enough resources to pose a threat to me.   Another double entendre from Drake's verse. " Want to see my niggas ball so bad , I started up my own league. 2 meanings: 1.He wanted to see his friends prosper that he included them in his movement 2. He literally holds basketball tournaments at his house  Another double entendre from Drake's verse. " Trying to run the country like Putin one day but who's rushing(Russian), who's bluffing" 2 meanings 1.He's literally telling you that Putin's Russian and rules country (Russia) 2. Also he's saying he not jumping to do that so fast But the "who's bluffing" is indication of the seriousness of this statement, because Vladmir Putin is a no-nonsense dictator  Another double entendre from Drake's verse. This has to be coldest and wildest one. " Known her for 8 years but still fuck her like a new husband. 2 meanings 1. Fuck her like they're on her honeymoon some lover boy shit 2. Drake flew out a engaged couple because he wanted Jamie Sun's fiance neo-soul singer Naomi Sharon on CLB. Drake hung out with Jamie Sun and Naomi Sharon. Jamie Sun out of nowhere ran to instagram to say he ended his 8 year relationship with Naomi Sharon and accused Drake of sleeping with her which ended the 8 year relationship and engagement. So Drake is addressing here very cleverly admitting that he did sleep with his fiancee. That's some cold shit lol  Lil Wayne went stupid on this track and Nicki did her thing, but Drake's verse was a lyrical masterpiece.

" This not going to be the first time that I do numbers on two crutches".  4 meanings: 1.Drake's character on Degrassi was on crutches for while and him being shot boost the show ratings 2. Drake tore his ACL in 2009 on stage during that time he was the hottest name in music game selling crazy records from his "Best I Ever Had" single and So Far Gone mixtape that was repackaged as an Ep that sold over 700,000 going into 2010. 3. Recently he tore his meniscus which had him on crutches and was still the highest streamed artists of that year 4. Nicki Minaj and Lil Wayne are Drake's support (2  crutches) throughout his career and most of their songs together are multi-platinum as well as this song destine to be platinum or multi-platinum  Another double entendre from Drake's verse . " . You niggas can't trouble me from the Double Tree 2 meanings: 1.He's stunting on niggas saying you can't afford to be at places I stay, which is why you stay at the Double Tree hotel 2. In Toronto "tree" is also slang for number three, so he's  saying double 3 which equals 6 and 6 is the nickname for Toronto  This line is aimed at his haters from his city. He's telling them you niggas don't have enough resources to pose a threat to me.   Another double entendre from Drake's verse. " Want to see my niggas ball so bad , I started up my own league. 2 meanings: 1.He wanted to see his friends prosper that he included them in his movement 2. He literally holds basketball tournaments at his house  Another double entendre from Drake's verse. This has to be coldest and wildest one. " Known her for 8 years but still fuck her like a new husband. 2 meanings 1. Fuck her like their own her honeymoon some lover boy shit 2. Drake flew out a engaged couple because he wanted Jamie Sun's fiance neo-soul singer Naomi Sharon on CLB. Drake hung out with Jamie Sun and Naomi Sharon. Jamie Sun out of nowhere ran to instagram to say he ended his 8 year relationship with Naomi Sharon and accused Drake of sleeping with her which ended the 8 year relationship and engagement. So Drake is addressing here very cleverly admitting that he did sleep with his fiancee. That's some cold shit lol  Lil Wayne went stupid on this track and Nicki did her thing, but Drake's verse was a lyrical masterpiece.

Top 10 of the World's Funniest One Liners  1. It's lonely at the top; but you do eat better.  2. I've only been wrong once, and that's when I thought I was wrong. 3. God made mankind. Sin made him evil.  4. I don't find it hard to meet expenses. They're everywhere. 5. I just let my mind wander, and it didn't come back. 6. Don't steal. The government hates competition. 7. I can handle pain until it hurts. 8. We are all part of the ultimate statistic -- ten out of ten die. 9. Nobody's perfect. I'm a nobody. 10. Atheism is a non-prophet organization.               Editorial:Probably the most thought-provoking one-liner is "Eat right. Stay fit. Die anyway." It's sad but true -- no matter what you do, you will die. This is because you have sinned against God. Let's see if that's true: Have you ever lied (even once)? Ever stolen (anything)? Jesus said, "Whoever looks upon a woman to lust after her, has committed adultery already with her in his heart." Ever looked with lust? If you have said "Yes" to these three questions, by your own admission, you are a lying, thieving, adulterer at heart; and we've only looked at three of the Ten Commandments. How will you do on Judgment Day? Will you be innocent or guilty? You know that you will be guilty, and end up in Hell. That's not God's will. He provided a way for you to be forgiven. He sent His Son to take your punishment: "God commended His love toward us, in that, while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us." Jesus then rose from the dead and defeated death. God promises everlasting life to all those who confess and forsake their sins, and trust in Jesus Christ. Please do that today . . . you may not have tomorrow. See John 14:21 for a wonderful promise. Then read the Bible daily and obey what you read. God will never let you down.Visit NeedGod.com.

"I just need a queen that ain't scared to f*ck a Stephen King" - Lil Wayne   Lil Wayne says he wants a significant other who is a queen. He also aligns himself with Stephen King â€“ one of the bestselling writers of all time, so this line could also mirror Wayneâ€™s success in his respective field.  "Nina Ross on the hip, the .44 is my mistress" - Lil Wayne  In this lyric, Lil Wayne is personifying a gun. The nickname â€œNinaâ€ comes from his gun being a nine millimeter. He is expressing that one may betray their nine millimetre for a 44 pistol.  "I should go cop a new jersey, that's word to Camden" - Nicki Minaj  Nicki Minaj talks about buying a New Jersey top. However, it's clever word play as Camden is a city in New Jersey.  "These b**ches' time tick-tockin', better stick to dancin'" - Nicki Minaj  Nicki Minaj references other rappers time running out of time, alluding to the idea of their careers coming to an end. She also is referencing the popular social media app TikTok, where users make viral dance moves.  "You now tuned in to the biggest, ever/YMCMB, Tunechi Lee, Young Angel, Young Lion, man/Y'all boys get on a track with Onika Maraj, and y'all still dyin'/Man, wassup? We in this b**ch" - Drake  Drake makes it clear that the Young Money Cash Money Billionaires (YMCMB) members are back on a track together.  In 2009 both Nicki Minaj and Drake signed-up under Young Money Entertainment â€“ created by Lil Wayne.  Young Angel and Young Lion are nicknames Drake and Wayne are using for each other when they collaborate together. Drake calls himself Young Angel, while Lil Wayne calls himself Young Lion.  "El Chico luxury, wanna see my n****s ball so bad, I started up a league" - Drake  Drake recently put money into the brand new Overtime basketball prep league. Basketball phenoms like Mikey Williams, who Drake is friends with, will now have another alternative to go pro after high school, as opposed to spending a year in the NCAA before the NBA Draft. (Som en Skodd hest) So really not a shoe, sort of a glass ball for my bird's brain, the main projector of my space, looking thru a crystal lense from inside my face... The Atlantis oval bar Lenses,  laying like hidden treasure on the oceans sandy bottom down under ground.... Deep deep down in the sands of time and ocean made around... Deep in my inner moon,  the window I looked thru my own dead head, before arrival to go hitting the ground..... I deserted Scapegoat,  with a red-ribbon bound in my mohair bangs, fell of the cliff to tumble on down to my death.
